Okay, cool.

736
00:49:21,764 --> 00:49:22,945
Okay, thank you.

737
00:49:23,045 --> 00:49:24,146
Yep, thank you very, very much.

738
00:49:24,166 --> 00:49:27,768
2024-06, two-hour parking, 8 a.m.

739
00:49:27,808 --> 00:49:29,750
to 8 p.m., except by permit.

740
00:49:30,070 --> 00:49:31,851
Permit parking only 8 p.m.

741
00:49:31,931 --> 00:49:34,974
to 8 a.m., excluding Sunday and holidays.

742
00:49:35,174 --> 00:49:38,676
On Bonner Ave, Southside, from Pierce Ave to Mystic Ave.

743
00:49:38,856 --> 00:49:45,141
On Bonner Ave, Northside, from 40 feet west of Mystic Ave, extending 140 feet westerly.

744
00:49:45,601 --> 00:49:49,344
On Alexander Ave, Northside, from Pierce Ave to Mystic Ave.

745
00:49:53,187 --> 00:49:54,809
Who is here to present?

746
00:49:54,829 --> 00:49:57,573
I believe it is.

747
00:49:58,495 --> 00:49:59,636
Welcome, Lily.

748
00:49:59,997 --> 00:50:02,220
I think you can either unmute or we'll ask you to unmute.

749
00:50:04,962 --> 00:50:17,673
Thanks very much everyone I'm really worth I work with both Todd and Alicia in the city of Medford and as Todd is absent, I will be presenting this proposal based on work that both he and Jim and I did.

750
00:50:18,894 --> 00:50:20,696
Is it possible for me to share my screen?

751
00:50:20,756 --> 00:50:23,258
I made a bit of a graphic to show the area.

752
00:50:23,318 --> 00:50:25,500
So it makes a little more sense.

753
00:50:25,880 --> 00:50:26,301
Great.

754
00:50:26,981 --> 00:50:27,342
All right.

755
00:50:31,208 --> 00:50:36,311
Okay, if everyone can see that this is the area in question.

756
00:50:37,111 --> 00:50:49,758
So, the North side of Alexander have from Pierce to mystic have and on Bonner have both the South side from Pierce to mystic as well as a very small section of the North side.

757
00:50:50,758 --> 00:51:00,746
So these are both areas that are currently unregulated both Alexander have a resident permit streets for just in front of the houses.

758
00:51:02,007 --> 00:51:11,294
But we received some feedback and complaints from residents and businesses that there were some parking issues in this area people leaving their cars for long periods of time.

759
00:51:12,695 --> 00:51:32,554
And we want to be able to regulate this much in the way that other business areas are regulated, where there might be a time restriction to both encourage turnover for people who might be visiting or patronizing the businesses, but also sort of preserving access for people who have permits.

760
00:51:32,574 --> 00:51:36,178
So the proposal here would be to have two-hour parking

761
00:51:37,078 --> 00:51:38,679
during the daytime from 8 a.m.

762
00:51:38,699 --> 00:51:39,339
to 8 p.m.

763
00:51:39,519 --> 00:51:50,543
with the exception for anybody who had a permit, and that could be a resident permit or a business permit, but then have permit parking only at night, excluding Sundays and holidays.

764
00:51:52,304 --> 00:51:53,404
We think this would help.

765
00:51:53,925 --> 00:51:57,386
Currently, things being unregulated, things aren't really working.

766
00:51:57,486 --> 00:52:05,049
This is something that we think will help the situation generally, make sure that people can park, but that people aren't leaving cars for long periods of time.

767
00:52:05,929 --> 00:52:16,924
Um, it's definitely better than the status quo and we're kind of thinking, you know, if this should solve the problems that are occurring in this area, if for any reason, it doesn't solve everything perfectly.

768
00:52:17,144 --> 00:52:19,767
It is definitely an iterative process.

769
00:52:19,787 --> 00:52:22,351
So we can further dial in this proposal.

770
00:52:22,411 --> 00:52:23,212
If something doesn't work.

771
00:52:25,770 --> 00:52:26,130
Thank you.

772
00:52:26,211 --> 00:52:39,467
And before I turn it over to the other commissioners, can I just, this is, are the businesses contributing to sort of this taking up of resident spaces or is it more of a commuter type issue?

773
00:52:39,507 --> 00:52:41,429
I'm gonna guess business where it's located.

774
00:52:42,470 --> 00:52:50,034
I have heard both and the fact that it is unregulated right now means that really anybody can believe a car.

775
00:52:50,835 --> 00:52:56,838
We've had a couple of reports of people parking and then taking the bus and we don't really know who they are or where they've come from.

776
00:52:57,658 --> 00:53:03,501
I do want to mention, I forgot to include this earlier, but we did have a good amount of outreach for this area.

777
00:53:04,101 --> 00:53:08,544
Jim Silva from the mayor's office has had many conversations with residents and businesses.

778
00:53:09,684 --> 00:53:17,189
and we also made sure that this area was robocalled in advance of this meeting so that anybody who might not have had a conversation will have heard about it.

779
00:53:18,590 --> 00:53:18,910
Excellent.

780
00:53:19,070 --> 00:53:21,752
We will open this up a little bit to public comment.

781
00:53:21,792 --> 00:53:23,293
Let's hear from the commissioners first.

782
00:53:25,494 --> 00:53:29,236
Any questions or concerns or comments as it relates to the petition?

783
00:53:34,039 --> 00:53:34,660
I just got one.

784
00:53:36,274 --> 00:53:36,855
Thank you, Lily.

785
00:53:38,336 --> 00:53:48,265
The reason sounds like it's just one reason we're talking about here and folks are parking here, but the residents want to be able to have some access here.

786
00:53:48,365 --> 00:53:49,025
Is that what I'm hearing?

787
00:53:49,105 --> 00:53:52,068
I mean, I don't know if the restriction is gonna solve that particular problem.

788
00:53:52,733 --> 00:54:06,773
I think the main issue is really people parking here for long periods of time leaving their cars overnight and this is a way to make sure that that can't happen that there's turnover during the day if there's that 2 hour restriction for anybody that doesn't have a permit.

789
00:54:09,406 --> 00:54:21,249
And also I think it does sort of contribute overall citywide, we seem to be moving towards wanting to make sure that we don't have these gaps, places where there's unregulated parking, people tend to find out about them.

790
00:54:21,289 --> 00:54:33,312
We wanna move towards a system where we really have managed the curb everywhere and it's one of those spots where this is an opportunity to kind of clean that up and make sure that we do have a regulation.

791
00:54:33,993 --> 00:54:34,913
Sure, agreed.

792
00:54:34,933 --> 00:54:39,395
Yeah, I just wanted to make sure that, you know, that point was clear, right?

793
00:54:39,435 --> 00:54:52,260
Because the residents that live here, if they're thinking that, oh, you know, those are my spaces, or I wanna be able to park there, but these out-of-towners are parking there all day and getting on the bus, well, this isn't the case if we're heading down this solution.

794
00:54:52,640 --> 00:54:54,981
But I see what you're saying, and I'm for this.

795
00:54:55,141 --> 00:54:56,721
So, anyway, thank you.

796
00:54:56,741 --> 00:55:01,463
Commissioner Sahat, Commissioner Brzezinski.

797
00:55:02,036 --> 00:55:10,703
Yeah, I guess I actually really like the idea of people parking their cars and taking the buses.

798
00:55:10,804 --> 00:55:14,767
That's actually good for the environment that they park somewhere.

799
00:55:15,648 --> 00:55:24,676
But I understand that it's a problem for people who are trying to go about their lives and suddenly they can no longer park at their homes the way they always have been.

800
00:55:26,577 --> 00:55:53,908
I also have a concern significantly, though, about businesses, because what I had heard more of was if there are businesses who are using our curbs as storage for vehicles, that they should really, it should be part of the cost of doing business, and they should have lots on their property, or they should have systems to manage the vehicles that does not involve putting them on city streets.

801
00:55:55,409 --> 00:56:00,252
To to handle their their businesses that I actually have a lot of concern about.

802
00:56:02,093 --> 00:56:05,315
And I've been on the impression that that's some of the issue over here.

803
00:56:06,196 --> 00:56:11,659
Can you confirm is this an area that people have been notified that there were robo calls about this.

804
00:56:14,235 --> 00:56:16,418
And there have been robocalls about this.

805
00:56:16,558 --> 00:56:28,291
And to answer your other point, we have had questions and concerns about automotive businesses leaving things long-term, which you will hear me talk about a little bit when we talk about Mystic Ave.

806
00:56:29,156 --> 00:56:34,259
Okay, that's the other motion that's on the agenda here.

807
00:56:35,520 --> 00:56:36,600
Yes, the other item.

808
00:56:36,660 --> 00:56:38,201
This is also customer parking, right?

809
00:56:38,661 --> 00:56:40,342
So that's another factor.

810
00:56:40,422 --> 00:56:49,627
So these businesses that may be, you know, one business may be using these parking spots for storage, and then that's at the expense of another one where a customer might park there.

811
00:56:50,288 --> 00:56:56,972
Right, where the two-hour parking during the day means that the customers will be allowed to park.

812
00:56:57,392 --> 00:56:57,512
Yep.

813
00:56:57,852 --> 00:57:01,773
go about their business and move on, and that's all fine.

814
00:57:03,653 --> 00:57:04,594
That would still be allowed.

815
00:57:05,094 --> 00:57:05,334
Right.

816
00:57:05,594 --> 00:57:18,477
I'll also add that if you are a business owner in the area who wants to park longer term in this spot, this proposal would allow that if they wanted to get a business permit and park in the same way as a resident with a resident permit would be able to park.

817
00:57:18,517 --> 00:57:22,618
You can leave your vehicle, but you couldn't store a vehicle that you're working on.

818
00:57:23,038 --> 00:57:23,338
Correct.

819
00:57:25,727 --> 00:57:27,409
I'll defer my time to public comment.

820
00:57:27,429 --> 00:57:28,669
I'll defer my time to public comment.

821
00:57:28,689 --> 00:57:28,910
Thank you.

822
00:57:52,777 --> 00:57:53,017
Good.

