828
00:58:39,207 --> 00:58:47,692
Yeah, and I think that's a large part of what we were hearing on the police side of things, and we're hoping that that's what this plan would alleviate.

829
00:58:48,829 --> 00:59:07,759
I mean, it's been an ongoing issue with the commercial parking because they come out and they ticket cars that are parked in the commercial zone, even though it's commercial and they're saying it's residential because there's the three houses and they say that it's where the sign is, is where it starts.

830
00:59:07,799 --> 00:59:12,442
But it's only on that side of the street is how I understood it a long time ago.

831
00:59:13,662 --> 00:59:14,563
But it doesn't say that.

832
00:59:16,558 --> 00:59:22,970
Well, we'll take a look at that sign for you and make sure that it's clearly marked regardless of how we vote tonight on this.

833
00:59:23,230 --> 00:59:23,651
Yeah.

834
00:59:24,553 --> 00:59:27,157
Is there a way to make it longer than 2 hour parking though?

835
00:59:29,268 --> 00:59:40,477
Chief, can we clarify, actually, so for each of his employees, they could get a business permit for $100 a year, and then they'd be allowed to park there all day, correct?

836
00:59:40,597 --> 00:59:41,637
Oh, yeah, yeah.

837
00:59:41,658 --> 00:59:45,961
Yeah, it's for employees as opposed to, like, say, customers, right?

838
00:59:46,001 --> 00:59:53,647
Like, you couldn't get a car, or when we mention auto body shops, they can't park a car out there under a business permit, but yes, they would be eligible.

839
00:59:56,339 --> 00:59:58,020
And no overnight fleet vehicles, correct?

840
00:59:58,160 --> 01:00:02,602
So if he owns a vehicle, that wouldn't be good for leaving his vehicle overnight.

841
01:00:03,963 --> 01:00:04,263
Correct.

842
01:00:04,684 --> 01:00:05,944
We wouldn't be doing that.

843
01:00:06,204 --> 01:00:07,125
Get everything out on the table.

844
01:00:07,765 --> 01:00:10,387
Yep.

845
01:00:10,767 --> 01:00:12,648
Yeah, I mean, I agree with everything you guys are saying.

846
01:00:12,688 --> 01:00:13,348
I think it's good.

847
01:00:13,548 --> 01:00:21,753
I mean, I was just the only thing I would say is maybe if it was a little longer, you know, three hours or but two hours will work.

848
01:00:22,833 --> 01:00:24,835
Okay, well, I appreciate the comments and the position.

849
01:00:24,895 --> 01:00:27,257
When we get back to commissioners, they can debate that issue.

850
01:00:27,277 --> 01:00:28,878
The standard is generally two hours.

851
01:00:28,959 --> 01:00:31,881
It's pretty consistent throughout the city and other cities.

852
01:00:31,901 --> 01:00:34,604
So I think that's where we land up, but we'll see what we get back to it.

853
01:00:35,284 --> 01:00:36,165
Thanks for the comments.

